    "MPA trained with more counterfactual steps results in better test-time performance, as the Q value model takes more future steps as the supervision signals.in Table 6 (left).",
    "Compared to the in-domain results in Table 1, we can see a significantly degraded performance in AD-MLP and Diffusion, while the pretrained E2E policies still perform similarly as they do in the in-domain scenes.",
    "We observe that the MPA agents built upon the pretrained E2E policies are still optimal and quite robust under the unseen scenes.",
    "All three variants have comparable HDScore with their in-domain evaluation.",
    "This demonstrates the generalizability of the proposed adapter and value model under unseen scene contexts."
